ytic philosophy at large. This double interpretational shift has allowed James to keep a fair amount of visibility on the academic scene but, over the years, it has significantly obliterated his vision. It is time to rediscover James from the perspective of his radical empiricism.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 08. Jul 2019) 0aPanpsychism. 0aPragmatism. 4aPragmatismus. 4aProzessphilosophie. 4aWhitehead. 4aWilliam James. 7aPHILOSOPHY / History & Surveys / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Philosophy English Language 2000-2014z978311023848808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Philosophy 2000 - 2014z9783110636949oZDB-23-GPH08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruyterteBook Package De Gruyter Ontos 2002-2012z978311033122608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruyterteBook Paket De Gruyter Ontos 2002-2012z9783110331219oZDB-23-DON0 cprintz978311032964340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110329766423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110329766.jpg  a978-3-11-023848-8  DGBA Backlist Philosophy English Language 2000-2014c2000d2014  a978-3-11-033122-6  eBook Package De Gruyter Ontos 2002-2012  aDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014c2000d2014  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA2HUM  aPDA5EBK  aPDA7ENG  aZDB-23-DONb2012  aZDB-23-GPHc2000d2014